rmwind Quartermaster - Revshon}}\n{{Zone Map Note|58.6|69.0||The Empty Quiver|Location::The Empty Quiver}}\n{{Zone Map Note|61.2|64.8|Barber|Barber|Tracking##Barber}}\n{{Zone Map Note|70.6|73.0|FlightMaster|Gryphon Roost|Tracking##FlightMaster;;Tracking::Gryphon Roost}}\n{{Zone Map Note|64.0|68.6||Weller's Arsenal|Location::Weller's Arsenal}}\n{{Zone Map Note|62.6|68.4||Lionheart Armory|Location::Lionheart Armory}}\n{{Zone Map Note|64.4|71.8||Everyday Merchandise|Location::Everyday Merchandise}}\n{{Zone Map Note|66.4|73.6||Trias' Cheese|Location::Trias' Cheese}}\n{{Zone Map Note|64.6|76.8|Tabard|Stormwind Visitor's Center - Guild matters|Services##Guild Services;;Services::Stormwind Visitor's Center - Guild matters}}\n{{Zone Map Note|63.6|74.6||Pestle's Apothecary|Location::Pestle's Apothecary}}\n{{Zone Map Note|62.6|77.6|Banker|Bank - Stormwind Counting House|Services##Banker;;Services::Bank - Stormwind Counting House}}\n{{Zone Map Note|60.8|74.8|Inn|The Gilded Rose|Services##Inn;;Services::The Gilded Rose}}\n{{Zone Map Note|61.6|71.0|Auctioneer|Auction House - Trader's House|Tracking##Auctioneer;;Tracking::Auction House - Trader's House}}\n{{Zone Map Note|71.6|57.8||Thane's Boots|Location::Thane's Boots}}\n{{Zone Map Note|69.4|57.6||The Silver Shield|Location::The Silver Shield}}\n{{Zone Map Note|73.2|57.2||Heavy Handed Weapons|Location::Heavy Handed Weapons}}\n{{Zone Map Note|76.0|53.4|Inn|Pig and Whistle Tavern|Services##Inn;;Services::Pig and Whistle Tavern}}\n{{Zone Map Note|77.0|57.6||Honest Blades|Location::Honest Blades}}\n{{Zone Map Note|77.0|61.2||Limited Immunity|Location::Limited Immunity}}\n{{Zone Map Note|71.8|62.8||The Protective Hide|Location::The Protective Hide}}\n{{Zone Map Note|73.6|60.0||Cutthroat Alley|Location::Cutthroat Alley}}\n{{Zone Map Note|74.2|58.0||The Five Deadly Venoms|Location::The Five Deadly Venoms}}\n{{Zone Map Note|76.6|65.6|POI46|Champions' Hall - Quartermasters|Faction##Alliance;;Faction::Champions' Hall - Quartermasters}}\n{{Zone Map Note|79.0|70.6|StableMaster|Command Center|Tracking##StableMaster;;Tracking::Command Center}}\n{{Zone Map Note|79.6|61.2||SI:7|Location::SI:7}}\n{{Zone Map Note|87.0|36.6|BattleMaster|Battlemasters|Tracking##BattleMaster;;Tracking::Battlemasters}}\n{{Zone Map Note|52.0|74.2|Diamond|Arcane Reforger - Ithurian; The Scribe of Stormwind|Point of Interest::Arcane Reforger - Ithurian; The Scribe of Stormwind}}\n{{Zone Map Note|59.8|77.4||Gallina Winery|Location::Gallina Winery}}\n{{Zone Map Note|58.2|67.0||Canal Tailor and Fit Shop|Location::Canal Tailor and Fit Shop}}\n{{Zone Map Note|63.6|61.6||Denman Family Jewelers|Location::Denman Family Jewelers}}\n{{Zone Map Note|69.6|71.4||Fragrant Flowers|Location::Fragrant Flowers}}\n{{Zone Map Note|23.2|36.8|Cross|The Assurance, docked boat - Repair/Reagents/General Goods/Food and Drink|Location::The Assurance, docked boat - Repair/Reagents/General Goods/Food and Drink}}\n{{Zone Map Note|50.8|67.0|Blue|The Stockade|Portal##Group;;Portal::The Stockade}}\n}}\n|}\n\n== Changes in Legion ==\n{{Legion-section}}\n{{Sectionstub}}\n\n== Changes in Mists of Pandaria ==\n{{Mists-section}}In Mists of Pandaria, Pandarens who joined the Alliance such as [[Aysa Cloudsinger]] and [[Jojo Ironbrow]] are on an island in Stormwind City, this is also were you can buy the Dragon Turtle mounts and teleport to [[Paw'don Village]].\n\n== Changes in Cataclysm ==\n{{Cata-section}}\n{{Sectionstub}}\n\n== Maps ==\n;Pre-Legion\n<gallery>\nstormwindmap2.jpg|Map in ''[[World of Warcraft]]''\nWorldMap-Stormwind.jpg|Map in ''[[World of Warcraft: Wrath of the Lich King|Wrath of the Lich King]]''\nWorldMap-StormwindCityCata.jpg|Map of Stormwind in ''Cataclysm''\n</gallery>\n\n;Current\n<gallery>\nWorldMap-StormwindCity.jpg|Map of Stormwind in ''Legion''\n</gallery>\n\n;Other\n<gallery>\nUnusedwestzone.JPG|The mountains north of Stormwind City.\nstormwindmap.jpg|An early map of Stormwind City.\nStormwindmapLoC.JPG|Map in ''[[Lands of Conflict]]''\nAzerothLoC.JPG|The region of Stormwind.\n</gallery>\n\n== Media ==\n=== Images ===\n;Pre-Cataclysm\n<gallery captionalign=\"left\">\nFile:Stormwindcitypicture.jpg|Entrance in Cataclysm\n</gallery>\n\n;Current\n<gallery captionalign=\"left\">\nStormwind city cataclysm cinematic.PNG|Stormwind City seen at Cataclysm cinematic.\nFile:Stormwind aerial view.jpg|Aerial view of Stormwind\nFile:Stormwind 070910 010639 - Kirkburn 12319.jpg|Trade District Bank\nFile:Stormwind 070910 010647 - Kirkburn 12319.jpg|Trade District Bank\nFile:Stormwind 070910 010706 - Kirkburn 12319.jpg|Trade District Bank\nFile:Stormwind 070910 003013 - Kirkburn 12319.jpg|Stormwind Keep entrance\nFile:Stormwind 071310 001421 - Kirkburn 12319.jpg|Stormwind Keep entrance\nFile:Stormwind 071210 232604 - Kirkburn 12319.jpg|A fountain in Old Town\nFile:Stormwind 071210 232927 - Kirkburn 12319.jpg|An apple tree in Old Town\nFile:Stormwind 071210 233649 - Kirkburn 12319.jpg|Stormwind Park\nFile:Stormwind-Keep.jpg|A nighttime view of the Stormwind City from the top of Stormwind Keep\nFile:The-Former-Stormwind-Gardens.jpg|The Former Stormwind Park\nStormwind City.jpg\nStormwind City Bulletin Board.jpg|The Bulletin Board in Stormwind's [[Trade District]] offers quests to [[Mount Hyjal]] and [[Vashj'ir]]\n</gallery>\n\n;Other\n<gallery>\nFile:StormwindKeepW1.JPG|Stormwind Keep being guarded during the First War.\nFile:Humans victorious.png|Human victory in the First War (WC1 human campaign).\nFile:Warcraft orcs and humans2.jpg|Stormwind Keep before its destruction in the First War.\nFile:Defender of the Crown victorious.png|The \"Defender of the Crown\" and new king of Azeroth after winning the First War (WC1 Human Campaign).\n150px-Perfect flag of Stormwind.jpg|Stormwind flag\n</gallery>\n\n=== Videos ===\n<gallery widths=\"415\"><!-- two wide at 1600 -->\nStormwind - World of Warcraft\nStormwind HD - World of Warcraft Cataclysm\nCataclysm Stormwind\n</gallery>\n\n== Notes ==\n* Stormwind City is the only Alliance capital that has an instance within the city borders. This is convenient for repairing and selling afterward.\n* Stormwind City contains the Officer barracks for the Alliance, and thus access to all the special PvP gear.\n* Stormwind City's role as a hangout for high-level players has fluctuated over the years. Since patch 1.10, it has risen in popularity compared to Ironforge (though this may vary by server). Stormwind City is now only two boat rides (or a tram ride) away from every other Alliance city as well as Northrend, making it extremely attractive to adventurers of all races. As of Cataclysm, the presence of portals to all of the 81-85 level zones makes Stormwind City even more attractive as a homebase for players.\n* [[Night elves]] and [[draenei]] on [[mechanostrider]]s can ride through the Stormwind bank door; all other Alliance [[mount]]s make these two races too high to fit.\n* Somewhat bizarrely, the barred instance portal said to be the entrance to the yet-to-be-implemented [[player housing]] appears to be on the opposite side of the wall from the moat.\n* Look into [[List of Stormwind NPCs]] for a list of questgivers in the area.\n* If you are a low level mana user and want to save gold, there is an endless supply of [[Ice Cold Milk]] scattered around Stormwind City in barrels. While it is arguably not worth the tedium of finding them for most races, a dwarf with treasure finding can effortlessly harvest a stack or two of milk quickly.\n* Stormwind City used to be a big target for Horde players to kite the end-game boss [[Lord Kazzak]] and then set him loose within the city. Kazzak has since been moved to [[Hellfire Peninsula]].\n* Stormwind City is arguably the largest city in the game after the addition of Stormwind Harbor. It is only rivaled by [[Silvermoon City]] and [[Shattrath City]]. [[Dalaran]] and [[Darnassus]] used to be some of the biggest, but they were measured otherwise.\n* Stormwind City has the largest area outside of Kalimdor inhabited by [[Night Elf|Night Elves]].\n* Stormwind City has the largest amount of [[High Elf|High Elves]] than any other area of the world, with the majority of the population living there.\n\n== Patch changes ==\n*{{Patch 5.0.4|note=Pandarian balloon floats near the [[Eastern Earthshrine]].}}\n*{{Patch 4.0.3a|note=Major redesign of the City, with alterations to almost every district and the destruction of the Park.}}\n* {{Patch 1.4.0|note=Patrolling scouts that can see through stealth and invisibility have been added to Stormwind City.}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Stormwind to Booty Bay travel guide]]\n\n== External links ==\n{{bnetwowzone|{{PAGENAME}}}}\n{{elinks-zone|1519}}\n\n;Old\n\n{{elink|icon=archive|site=Web.Archive.org|link=http://web.archive.org/web/20100807212705/http://www.worldofwarcraft.com/info/basics/cities.html#stormwind|desc=Major Cities - Stormwind City archived page (US)|bydate=(archived 7-Aug-2010)}}\n{{elink|icon=archive|site=Web.Archive.org|link=http://web.archive.org/web/20100923213717/http://www.wow-europe.com/en/info/basics/cities.html#stormwind|desc=The Major Cities - Stormwind City archived page (EU)|bydate=(archived 23-Sep-2010)}}\n\n\n\n{{Stormwind City}}\n{{Elwynn Forest}}\n{{Eastern Kingdoms}}\n{{Factions|state=collapsed}}\n\n[[de:Sturmwind (Stadt)]]\n[[es:Ciudad de Ventormenta]]\n[[fr:Hurlevent (Ville)]]\n[[pl:Stormwind (miasto)]]\n[[Category:Human territories]]\n[[Category:Stormwind City| ]]\n[[Category:Alliance cities]]\n[[Category:World of Warcraft: The Roleplaying Game]]\n[[Category:Lands of Conflict]]\n[[Category:More Magic and Mayhem]]"}}}